fix: align schemas to GBR 0.1.0 document format

- Update all schema $id URLs to gbr-protocol.dev/schemas/v0/
- Add missing enum values: beat_type (4), scene_function (3), tactic (2),
  trigger_type (1), emotion (resolve, longing, determination),
  spatial_structure (palimpsest, bounded), territory_type (protagonist_home,
  antagonist_domain), pov_role (participant, focalizer)
- Add new $defs: event_type, outcome_type, causal_role_type, role_in_scene,
  polarity_transition, arc_type
- scene-card: setting oneOf string/object; canonical_summary oneOf string/object;
  scene_turn $def; scene_number_in_chapter + focalization_type aliases;
  causal_role, stakes_domain, motif_tags, theory_notes, pov_role fields;
  slug patterns allow hyphens
- character-state: anyOf required (character_id or character_ref);
  add character_id, role_in_scene, arc_type, emotion, masked_emotion,
  tactic(nullable), epistemic_state; fix duplicate tactic definition;
  slug patterns allow hyphens
- story-architecture: genre accepts string slug or object
- conformance/valid: $schema URLs updated to include /v0/ path segment

All 5 scene-card examples now pass Level 1 (schema) validation.
